        "fields": {
          "id": "0-3_13",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 0,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 3,
          "moveOrder": 13,
          "role": "question",
          "voice": "Demons' question",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "לְבָתַר דִּנְפַק, אֲמַר לֵיהּ רַב חִסְדָּא",
          "endExcerpt": "יָדַע מָר",
          "summary": "After escaping, the demons ask Rav Chisda how he knew of the plot."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 3,
        "endSegIdx": 3,
        "fields": {
          "id": "0-3_14",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 0,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 3,
          "moveOrder": 14,
          "role": "answer",
          "voice": "Rav Chisda's answer",
          "rabbiNames": ["Rav Chisda"],
          "excerpt": "אֲמַר לֵיהּ: חֲדָא – דִּנְחַר לִי מָר",
          "endExcerpt": "דְּלָא מְעַלּוּ",
          "summary": "Rav Chisda explains he knew from three signs: his own snort, the child's verse, and the fact that servants are suspected of being dishonest."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 4,
        "endSegIdx": 5,
        "fields": {
          "id": "4-5_0",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 4,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 5,
          "moveOrder": 0,
          "role": "opening",
          "voice": "Gemara's interpretation",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "עָשִׂיתִי לִי שָׁרִים וְשָׁרוֹת",
          "endExcerpt": "שִׁידְּתָא",
          "summary": "The Gemara interprets the verse from Ecclesiastes, explaining 'sharim vesharon' as types of music, 'ta'anugot' as pools and bathhouses, and 'shidah veshidot' as male and female demons, with a Western alternative term 'shidta'."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 4,
        "endSegIdx": 5,
        "fields": {
          "id": "4-5_1",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 4,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 5,
          "moveOrder": 1,
          "role": "supporting-evidence",
          "voice": "Rabbi Yochanan",
          "rabbiNames": ["Rabbi Yochanan"],
          "excerpt": "אָמַר רַבִּי יוֹחָנָן",
          "endExcerpt": "מָה הִיא",
          "summary": "Rabbi Yochanan states that there were three hundred types of demons in Shichin, but he does not know what a female demon herself is."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 6,
        "endSegIdx": 7,
        "fields": {
          "id": "6-7_0",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 6,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 7,
          "moveOrder": 0,
          "role": "question",
          "voice": "Gemara's question",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "אָמַר מָר, הָכָא תַּרְגִּימוּ: שֵׁידָא וְשֵׁידְתִין",
          "endExcerpt": "לְמַאי אִיבְּעִי לֵיהּ?",
          "summary": "The Gemara asks why Solomon needed male and female demons (שֵׁדָה וְשֵׁידְתִין)."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 6,
        "endSegIdx": 7,
        "fields": {
          "id": "6-7_1",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 6,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 7,
          "moveOrder": 1,
          "role": "answer",
          "voice": "Gemara's explanation",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "דִּכְתִיב: ״וְהַבַּיִת בְּהִבָּנוֹתוֹ אֶבֶן שְׁלֵמָה מַסָּע נִבְנָה וְגוֹ׳״",
          "endExcerpt": "אֲמַרוּ לֵיהּ: אִיכָּא שָׁמִירָא דְּאַיְיתִי מֹשֶׁה לְאַבְנֵי אֵפוֹד",
          "summary": "The Gemara explains that when building the Temple, Solomon asked the Sages how to cut stones without iron, and they told him about the shamir worm that Moses used for the stones of the ephod."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 6,
        "endSegIdx": 7,
        "fields": {
          "id": "6-7_2",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 6,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 7,
          "moveOrder": 2,
          "role": "answer",
          "voice": "Sages' advice to Solomon",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "אֲמַר לְהוּ: הֵיכָא אִישְׁתְּכַח?",
          "endExcerpt": "דִּילְמָא אַשְׁמְדַאי – מַלְכָּא דְשֵׁידֵי, יָדַע",
          "summary": "The Sages advised Solomon to bring male and female demons and subdue them together, as they might know and reveal the location of the shamir; the demons said they did not know, but suggested that Ashmedai, the king of demons, might know."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 8,
        "endSegIdx": 8,
        "fields": {
          "id": "8-9_0",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 8,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 9,
          "moveOrder": 0,
          "role": "question",
          "voice": "Solomon's question to the demons",
          "rabbiNames": ["Solomon"],
          "excerpt": "אֲמַר לְהוּ: הֵיכָא אִיתֵיהּ?",
          "endExcerpt": "אָמְרִי לֵיהּ: אִיתֵיהּ בְּטוּרָא פְּלָן.",
          "summary": "Solomon asks the demons where Ashmedai is, and they reply that he is on a certain mountain."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 8,
        "endSegIdx": 8,
        "fields": {
          "id": "8-9_1",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 8,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 9,
          "moveOrder": 1,
          "role": "answer",
          "voice": "Demons' description of Ashmedai's routine",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "כַּרְיָא לֵיהּ בֵּירָא",
          "endExcerpt": "וְחָתֵים לֵיהּ וְאָזֵיל.",
          "summary": "The demons describe Ashmedai's daily routine: he ascends to heaven to study, descends to earth to study, then returns to check his seal, drink, and reseal it."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 9,
        "endSegIdx": 9,
        "fields": {
          "id": "8-9_2",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 8,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 9,
          "moveOrder": 2,
          "role": "resolution",
          "voice": "Solomon's plan and Benaiah's preparation",
          "rabbiNames": ["Solomon", "Benaiah ben Yehoyada"],
          "excerpt": "שַׁדְּרֵיהּ לִבְנָיָהוּ בֶּן יְהוֹיָדָע",
          "endExcerpt": "סְלֵיק יְתֵיב בְּאִילָנָא",
          "summary": "Solomon sends Benaiah ben Yehoyada with a chain engraved with the Name, a ring engraved with the Name, tufts of wool, and skins of wine; Benaiah digs a pit below, drains the water, plugs it with wool, digs a pit above, pours in wine, and covers it, then sits in a tree."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 10,
        "endSegIdx": 10,
        "fields": {
          "id": "10-11_0",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 10,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 11,
          "moveOrder": 0,
          "role": "opening",
          "voice": "Narrative (Ashmedai's arrival)",
          "rabbiNames": ["Ashmedai"],
          "excerpt": "כִּי אֲתָא סַיְירֵיהּ לְגוּשְׁפַּנְקָא",
          "endExcerpt": "לָא אִישְׁתִּי",
          "summary": "Ashmedai arrives, finds wine instead of water, and refuses to drink, citing verses against wine."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 11,
        "endSegIdx": 11,
        "fields": {
          "id": "10-11_1",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 10,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 11,
          "moveOrder": 1,
          "role": "resolution",
          "voice": "Narrative (Ashmedai's capture)",
          "rabbiNames": ["Ashmedai", "Benaiah ben Yehoyada"],
          "excerpt": "כִּי צָחֵי, לָא סַגִּיא לֵיהּ",
          "endExcerpt": "שְׁמָא דְּמָרָךְ עֲלָךְ",
          "summary": "Ashmedai becomes thirsty, drinks, falls asleep; Benaiah descends, chains him, and seals the chain with the Name."
        }
      },
      {
        "startSegIdx": 12,
        "endSegIdx": 12,
        "fields": {
          "id": "12-12_0",
          "sectionStartSegIdx": 12,
          "sectionEndSegIdx": 12,
          "moveOrder": 0,
          "role": "opening",
          "voice": "Narrator (Stam)",
          "rabbiNames": [],
          "excerpt": "כִּי נָקֵיט לֵיהּ וְאָתֵי",
          "endExcerpt": "נְפַקָא",
          "summary": "The narrative describes Ashmedai's violent journey as Benaiah leads him, uprooting a palm tree and destroying a house, until a widow comes out to beg him not to destroy her hut."
        }
      }
